Title: Input Data Coding in Multivariate Data Analysis: Techniques and Practice in Correspondence Analysis  
Author: F. MURTAGH and T.K. GOPALAN 
Keyword: Multivariate data analysis; Correspondence analysis; Dimensionality reduction; Data display  
Note: Preprint INFM-97-003,  
Address: Londonderry BT48 7JL, Northern Ireland  Vijayalakshmi Street, Mahalingapuram, Madras 600 034, India  Magee College  
Affiliation: Faculty of Informatics, University of Ulster,  21  University of Ulster, Faculty of Informatics,  
Email: Email fd.murtagh@ulst.ac.uk  
Web: URL www.infm.ulst.ac.uk/~fionn  
Date: 1997 May 16  
Abstract: SUMMARY We discuss input data coding issues, particularly in the context of exploratory multivariate data analysis. We provide a review of recent work associated with J.-P. Benzecri, which focuses on correspondence analysis and some other multivariate methods. Examples are provided to illustrate various current practices. Some extensions are also described of the use of such coding techniques to other work. SOMMAIRE Nous decrivons une gamme de techniques pratiques couramment utilisee en analyse des corre-spondances concernant le codage des donnees d'entree. Nous discutons des travaux recents de J.-P. Benzecri et de ses collaborateurs, en visant l'analyse des correspondances mais aussi d'autres methodes d'analyse des donnees telles que l'apprentissage par machine, les reseaux neuronaux, et la reconnaissance des formes. Plusieurs exemples sont utilises pour illustrer ces pratiques. Plusieurs generalisations de ces techniques de codage des donnees sont egalement decrites. 
